			<h2>Plugster</h2>
			<span class="work-type">iOS Native App</span>
		</div>
		<p class="item-description">
			Plugster is an iOS native app I developed as a side project to help electric vehicle owners know where to charge. This was driven
			by a real use-case I had where EV charging was limited near my place of work, and I would often arrive at one of the nearby
			chargers to find all plugs already in use. The app allowed users to view charging stations on a map, and to add favorite
			charging stations allowing for availability alerts, and geofenced push notifications to help the user choose which station
			to navigate to when entering a certain area. Plug availability was sourced from several sources, including an (at the time) new
			API from Tom Tom, and scraping public information from first-party sources like ChargePoint and Greenlots.
		</p>
