			<h2>Kiku</h2>
			<span class="work-type">Mobile/Desktop PWA</span>
		</div>
		<p class="item-description">
			Kiku is a personal music library hosting service and player app that I use every day. I built this for myself after Google Play Music, which I was
			using to host my personal music library, was discontinued. This started as a simple web page that would shuffle my music collection
			which I put in Amazon S3, and over time became a web app for managing my music library, and a mobile PWA for consumption on a mobile
			device. This project uses a NodeJS backend, MySQL, and has a lot of interesting hidden complexity. Audio is encoded to multiple
			quality levels asynchronously on upload, so the user can choose at which bitrate to stream. If multiple users upload the same audio,
			the audio is de-duped, but each user can still layer their own metadata on top. Tracks can be downloaded to the device for offline
			playback. The app is multi-tenant, but so far I've only been using it for myself. :)
		</p>
