			<h2>Astr</h2>
			<span class="work-type">JavaScript Library</span>
			<a class="work-link" href="https://github.com/fernap3/astr" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
		</div>
		<p class="item-description">
			Astr is a JavaScript test runner that I built during my time at Exago to allow us to easily run tests in either a NodeJS
			environment, or in Chromium depending on the requirements of the test.  At the time we were using a tool called Chutzpah
			to run our JavaScript unit tests in a browser environment, but this tool used an outdated version of Webkit and it was
			important for us to test in up-to-date versions of Chromium. So I built this library to run tests in Chromium using
			Puppeteer. Astr was integrated into our CI pipeline where it was used daily.
		</p>
		<div>
			<h2>node-mysql wrapper</h2>
			<span class="work-type">JavaScript Library</span>
			<a class="work-link" href="https://github.com/fernap3/node-mysql" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
		</div>
		<p class="item-description">
			This is a simple library I built for use in my personal projects. It puts a small wrapper around the popular node-mysql
			NPM package, allowing one to use JavaScript template literal syntax to build parameterized SQL queries. So a call like this:<br> 
			<code>doQuery(`SELECT col FROM table WHERE id=?`, [userId])</code><br>
			can instead look like this:<br>
			<code>doQuery(`SELECT col FROM table WHERE id=${userId}`)</code>.
		</p>
